page.title: 14Cutcombe Church.
page.content:
Cutcombe Church is very old although some parts have been rebuilt when they have needed it. There are many carvings on the stone pillars and also on the wooden choir stalls.
The tower is made of a different stone to the rest of the church and looks very different inside.
There is a list of the names of the men from the village who were killed in the two World Wars.
Not many people go to the church as there are not many people in the village and visitors do not see it as it is not near the main road.
